@csantanapr - I'm not able to merge due to the travis failure.   Travis only failed due to a timeout
`The job exceeded the maximum time limit for jobs, and has been terminated.`.  Up to that point all test cases had passed.  Since this is a new .md file with no associated test automation, it can be merged without green travis results.

@dzeyelid thanks for your feedback!
yes, this is an issue we are aware of. main point being that some commands have no good expression in ansible. the example you mentioned is a good instance of that: the ansible docker module does not yet support custom user namespaces (see issue https://github.com/ansible/ansible-modules-core/issues/5054). So here we had to manually call the docker cli. This has the drawback that you can not easily re-run the command. 

The intermediate solution we came up with is a "clean" mode of each playbook. By calling the same playbook with `-e mode=clean` you effectively undeploy the component you are calling.
